<component id="ID_txt04">
<text><![CDATA[<ul><li>Static NAT is for permanent one-to-one translations from a specific inside-local IP address to a specific inside-global IP address.</li><br/><li>Dynamic NAT assigns inside-global IP addresses on a first-come, first-served basis from an available pool of IP addresses to a designated network or sub-network. </li><br/><li>PAT, can be used to add a port number to the IP address for specific connections.</li><br/><li>Network devices that use NAT translate addresses on every packet. This can significantly increase processing work load.</li><br/><li>IPv6 incorporates a 128-bit addressing scheme, whereas IPv4 uses 32-bits.</li></ul>]]></text>
</component>

   
